Reasoning: The paper discusses the cybersecurity and cyberforensic consequences of secure, cloudless file transfer systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the P2P nature of these services, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also touches on the potential risks to corporate and governmental security, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and cybercrime (cs.CY).
